    "content_id":  "aac11c48-8cad-42a8-93ff-fd544accaa82",
    "description":  "Find out about bespoke testing legally required for certain types of work. ",
    "details":  {
                    "attachments":  [

                                    ],
                    "body":  "\u003cdiv class=\"govspeak\"\u003e\u003cp\u003eYou may need to take coronavirus (COVID-19) tests both before and after entering England from abroad. \u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/guidance/travel-to-england-from-another-country-during-coronavirus-covid-19\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eCheck the testing requirements for entering England from abroad\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eYou may be exempt from some or all COVID-19 travel and entry requirements because of your job.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/coronavirus-covid-19-travellers-exempt-from-uk-border-rules/coronavirus-covid-19-travellers-exempt-from-uk-border-rules\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eCheck if your job has travel exemptions\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf your job requires you to follow the bespoke testing regime, you must do so. It is a legal requirement (mandatory).\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThere are different rules if you’re:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003eactively working as a domestic sea fisherman or woman\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003ea diplomat\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003ea haulier\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eYou should check with your employer.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe bespoke testing programme you follow depends on the sector you work in.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eTesting will:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003eidentify cases of COVID-19, including variants\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003ehelp stop it spreading\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003ehelp you take suitable precautions to keep you and others safe\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv class=\"call-to-action\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/guidance/covid-19-coronavirus-restrictions-what-you-can-and-cannot-do\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eFollow the guidance on how to stay safe\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"what-you-need-to-do\"\u003eWhat you need to do\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eBefore you travel you must complete a \u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/provide-journey-contact-details-before-travel-uk\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003epassenger locator form\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eYou do not have to do this if you’re \u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/coronavirus-covid-19-travellers-exempt-from-uk-border-rules/coronavirus-covid-19-travellers-exempt-from-uk-border-rules\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eexempt\u003c/a\u003e from completing a passenger locator form.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eYou will not have to provide a testing booking reference on the form.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAt the border you’ll need to show evidence of the work you’ll be carrying out in England.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eYou can be fined up to £3,000 if you do not take a test when you are legally required to.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"where-to-get-a-bespoke-test\"\u003eWhere to get a bespoke test\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eYou can get a bespoke test at:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003eyour workplace – available to employers for employees who can’t work at home\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003ehome by \u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/order-coronavirus-rapid-lateral-flow-tests\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eordering test kits online\u003c/a\u003e or by calling 119\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003ea \u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/guidance/haulier-advice-site-locations\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003ehaulier advice site\u003c/a\u003e if you’re an HGV driver or operator\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"test-on-arrival\"\u003eTest on arrival\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf you do not qualify for fully vaccinated rules, and are travelling from a non-red list country, you must take a lateral flow test on or before day 2.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe day you arrive in England is day 0.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWhat else you must do depends on whether you’ve been in \u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/guidance/red-list-of-countries-and-territories\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003ea country on the red list\u003c/a\u003e in the 10 days before you arrive in England\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/guidance/travel-to-england-from-another-country-during-coronavirus-covid-19\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eCheck whether you qualify for fully vaccinated rules\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/coronavirus-covid-19-travellers-exempt-from-uk-border-rules/coronavirus-covid-19-travellers-exempt-from-uk-border-rules\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eCheck what bespoke testing programme you need to follow for your type of work\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf you do not qualify as fully vaccinated and are travelling every day, or for no more than 2 days at a time, you must also take a lateral flow test at least once every 3 days, unless you’re a haulier who is exempt from this requirement.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"text-reminders\"\u003eText reminders\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eYou’ll be sent text reminders to follow your bespoke testing programme from GOV.UK.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf you’re in the UK the text will be sent from:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003e44 (0)7984 404 870\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis may display as coming from a different number if you’ve left the UK or have a non-UK phone number.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"if-your-test-is-positive\"\u003eIf your test is positive\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThere is no longer a legal requirement for people with COVID-19 infection to self-isolate, however if you have any of the main symptoms of COVID-19 or a positive test result, the public health advice is to stay at home and avoid contact with other people.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIt is advised that you do not travel, including to leave the UK.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eFollow the guidance for households with possible or confirmed COVID-19 infection.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eYou will have to take a follow-up PCR test to check for new variants. You’ll have to buy this test from a \u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/list-of-private-providers-of-coronavirus-testing\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eprivate testing provider\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"check-general-travel-rules\"\u003eCheck general travel rules\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/guidance/travel-to-england-from-another-country-during-coronavirus-covid-19\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eRead the standard rules for entering England from abroad\u003c/a\u003e if you do not have a job with travel exemptions.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e",
